    {
      "text": "Zool: Majū Tsukai Densetsu (ズール 魔獣使い伝説, Zool: Legend of the Beast Tamer) is a role-playing video game for the Nintendo 64. It was released in 1999 in Japan only.\nThe gameplay is similar to Pokémon in that it shares the same concept of catching monsters. The player's character finds a monster and raises it to battle evil. The towns are presented in a top down view. The houses, inns, bars, dungeons and shops are fixed points the players can put a cursor over. The battle system features a bar of musical notes that the player uses to command the monsters. The players can carry up to four monsters at a time.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
